This is a platform game based upon Box2D physics engine and for Linux platforms, with mostly academic purposes, and it requires Box2D, OpenGL, libsdl-mixer, libpng and SOIL so far.

Installing libsdl-mixer is fairly easy. In any Debian-based system it's an available package in the official apt repositories.

For OpenGL, a quick an efficient installing guide can be found here: cacs.usc.edu/education/cs596/ogl_setup.pdf

For Box2D, you have to go to http://code.google.com/p/box2d/ to download it and follow the installing instructions contained in the file "Building.txt". 

For SOIL, installation is quite easy and code is obtained at http://www.lonesock.net/soil.html

After that, Makefile is available in the Debug folder. It's generated automatically by Eclipse.
